---
name: commands-to-hooks
description: Use when asked to convert CLAUDE.md instructions into git hooks or bash enforcement scripts
allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, AskUserQuestion
---

Take the instructions in the `CLAUDE.md` file, turn them into deterministic Claude Code hooks in this project directory. Not all instructions will be deterministic. Only do the ones you can, such as instructions to use one CLI command over another or disallowing certain CLI commands. Use separate bash scripts for running the hooks. For example:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
if command -v npm &> /dev/null
then
  echo "npm is installed"
else
  echo "npm is not installed"
fi
```

First, confirm with the user which hooks will be created. Second, implement the hooks. Third, provide the user with instructions on how to test the newly created hooks.
